article.headline: E. Illinois 28, Jacksonville St. 20
article.story: EDs: APNewsNow. Eastern Illinois 28, Jacksonville State 20. JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Lorence Ricks had three big special teams plays to lead Eastern Illinois to a 28-20 win over Jacksonville State on Saturday. Ricks returned a kickoff 87 yards late in the third quarter to give the Panthers a 28-13 lead. He also blocked a punt early in the second quarter and forced a fumble on a Gamecocks' punt return in the fourth. Ricks finished with 124 yards on two kick returns, became the first to score on a kickoff return against Jacksonville State since Eastern Illinois' Quentin Ponius on Nov. 10, 2007. He also returned a punt 26 yards. Jake Christensen was 16 of 29 with 190 yards and two touchdowns for the Panthers (6-2, 4-1 Ohio Valley Conference). The Gamecocks (4-3, 2-1) were led by Ryan Perrilloux, who threw for 236 yards on 16-of-26 passing. James Wilkerson caught Perrilloux's only touchdown pass and finished with 96 yards on five catches.
